{{Vocab-stub}}

There are two official '''languages of [[Norfolk Island]]''', English and [[Norfuk language|Norfuk]].  English, due to the influence of [[Great Britain]] and [[Australia]], the two [[colonialism|colonial powers]] who administered Norfolk Island, is the dominant language of the pair.  Norfuk, a creole language based on English and [[Tahitian language|Tahitian]] and brought to the island by the descendants of the [[Mutiny on the Bounty|Bounty mutineers]] from [[Pitcairn Island]] was spoken by 580 persons according to the 1989 census. It is closely related to [[Pitkern]] spoken on Pitcairn Island.

